Ntuthuko Shoba the alleged mastermind behind the murder of Tshegofatso Pule claims the alleged hitman was in a relationship with the victim. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Ntuthuko Shoba, the alleged mastermind behind the murder of Tshegofatso Pule, claims he uncovered new evidence that she was involved with her killer. READ: Tshegofatso Pule case back in court Shoba says he learned that Muzikayise Malephane was in a romantic relationship with Pule through a confession he made to Shoba’s cellmate. The awaiting-trial prisoner also wrote an affidavit detailing how he became friends with Malephane before he confessed to him.